88/*******************************************************************************
89 *
90 * FUNCTION: RsGetBufferDataLength
91 *
92 * PARAMETERS: InitializerOp - Current parse op, start of the resource
93 * descriptor
94 *
95 * RETURN: Length of the data buffer
96 *
97 * DESCRIPTION: Get the length of a RawDataBuffer, used for vendor data.
98 *
99 ******************************************************************************/
100
101static UINT16
102RsGetBufferDataLength (
103 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *InitializerOp)
104{
105 UINT16 ExtraDataSize = 0;
106 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *DataList;
107
108
109 /* Find the byte-initializer list */
110
111 while (InitializerOp)
112 {
113 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode == PARSEOP_DATABUFFER)
114 {
115 /* First child is the optional length (ignore it here) */
116
117 DataList = InitializerOp->Asl.Child;
118 DataList = ASL_GET_PEER_NODE (DataList);
119
120 /* Count the data items (each one is a byte of data) */
121
122 while (DataList)
123 {
124 ExtraDataSize++;
125 DataList = ASL_GET_PEER_NODE (DataList);
126 }
127
128 return (ExtraDataSize);
129 }
130
131 InitializerOp = ASL_GET_PEER_NODE (InitializerOp);
132 }
133
134 return (ExtraDataSize);
135}

138/*******************************************************************************
139 *
140 * FUNCTION: RsGetInterruptDataLength
141 *
142 * PARAMETERS: InitializerOp - Current parse op, start of the resource
143 * descriptor
144 * StartIndex - Start index of interrupt/pin list
145 *
146 * RETURN: Length of the interrupt data list
147 *
148 * DESCRIPTION: Get the length of a list of interrupt DWORDs for the GPIO
149 * descriptors.
150 *
151 ******************************************************************************/
152
153static UINT16
154RsGetInterruptDataLength (
155 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *InitializerOp,
156 UINT32 StartIndex)
157{
158 UINT16 InterruptLength;
159 UINT32 i;
160
161
162 /* Count the interrupt numbers */
163
164 InterruptLength = 0;
165 for (i = 0; InitializerOp; i++)
166 {
167 InitializerOp = ASL_GET_PEER_NODE (InitializerOp);
168
169 /* Interrupt list starts at offset StartIndex (Gpio descriptors) */
170
171 if (i >= StartIndex)
172 {
173 InterruptLength += 2;
174 }
175 }
176
177 return (InterruptLength);
178}

181/*******************************************************************************
182 *
183 * FUNCTION: RsGetVendorData
184 *
185 * PARAMETERS: InitializerOp - Current parse op, start of the resource
186 * descriptor.
187 * VendorData - Where the vendor data is returned
188 * DescriptorOffset - Where vendor data begins in descriptor
189 *
190 * RETURN: TRUE if valid vendor data was returned, FALSE otherwise.
191 *
192 * DESCRIPTION: Extract the vendor data and construct a vendor data buffer.
193 *
194 ******************************************************************************/
195
196static BOOLEAN
197RsGetVendorData (
198 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *InitializerOp,
199 UINT8 *VendorData,
200 ACPI_SIZE DescriptorOffset)
201{
202 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *BufferOp;
203 UINT32 SpecifiedLength = ACPI_UINT32_MAX;
204 UINT16 ActualLength = 0;
205
206
207 /* Vendor Data field is always optional */
208
209 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode == PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
210 {
211 return (FALSE);
212 }
213
214 BufferOp = InitializerOp->Asl.Child;
215 if (!BufferOp)
216 {
217 AslError (ASL_ERROR, ASL_MSG_SYNTAX, InitializerOp, "");
218 return (FALSE);
219 }
220
221 /* First child is the optional buffer length (WORD) */
222
223 if (BufferOp->Asl.ParseOpcode != PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
224 {
225 SpecifiedLength = (UINT16) BufferOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
226 }
227
228 /* Insert field tag _VEN */
229
230 RsCreateByteField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_VENDORDATA,
231 (UINT16) DescriptorOffset);
232
233 /* Walk the list of buffer initializers (each is one byte) */
234
235 BufferOp = RsCompleteNodeAndGetNext (BufferOp);
236 if (BufferOp->Asl.ParseOpcode != PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
237 {
238 while (BufferOp)
239 {
240 *VendorData = (UINT8) BufferOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
241 VendorData++;
242 ActualLength++;
243 BufferOp = RsCompleteNodeAndGetNext (BufferOp);
244 }
245 }
246
247 /* Length validation. Buffer cannot be of zero length */
248
249 if ((SpecifiedLength == 0) ||
250 ((SpecifiedLength == ACPI_UINT32_MAX) && (ActualLength == 0)))
251 {
252 AslError (ASL_ERROR, ASL_MSG_BUFFER_LENGTH, InitializerOp, NULL);
253 return (FALSE);
254 }
255
256 if (SpecifiedLength != ACPI_UINT32_MAX)
257 {
258 /* ActualLength > SpecifiedLength -> error */
259
260 if (ActualLength > SpecifiedLength)
261 {
262 AslError (ASL_ERROR, ASL_MSG_LIST_LENGTH_LONG, InitializerOp, NULL);
263 return (FALSE);
264 }
265
266 /* ActualLength < SpecifiedLength -> remark */
267
268 else if (ActualLength < SpecifiedLength)
269 {
270 AslError (ASL_REMARK, ASL_MSG_LIST_LENGTH_SHORT, InitializerOp, NULL);
271 return (FALSE);
272 }
273 }
274
275 return (TRUE);
276}

279/*******************************************************************************
280 *
281 * FUNCTION: RsGetStringDataLengthAt
282 *
283 * PARAMETERS: InitializerOp - Start of a subtree of init nodes
284 * StartIndex - Starting index of the string node
285 *
286 * RETURN: Valid string length if a string node is found at given
287 * StartIndex or 0 otherwise.
288 *
289 * DESCRIPTION: In a list of peer nodes, find the first one at given index
290 * that contains a string and return length.
291 *
292 ******************************************************************************/
293
294static UINT16
295RsGetStringDataLengthAt (
296 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *InitializerOp,
297 UINT32 StartIndex)
298{
299 UINT32 i;
300
301 for (i = 0; InitializerOp; i++)
302 {
303 if (i == StartIndex &&
304 InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode == PARSEOP_STRING_LITERAL)
305 {
306 return ((UINT16) (strlen (InitializerOp->Asl.Value.String) + 1));
307 }
308
309 InitializerOp = ASL_GET_PEER_NODE (InitializerOp);
310 }
311
312 return (0);
313}

316/*******************************************************************************
317 *
318 * FUNCTION: RsDoGpioIntDescriptor
319 *
320 * PARAMETERS: Info - Parse Op and resource template offset
321 *
322 * RETURN: Completed resource node
323 *
324 * DESCRIPTION: Construct a long "GpioInt" descriptor
325 *
326 ******************************************************************************/
327
328ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *
329RsDoGpioIntDescriptor (
330 ASL_RESOURCE_INFO *Info)
331{
332 AML_RESOURCE *Descriptor;
333 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *InitializerOp;
334 ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *Rnode;
335 char *ResourceSource = NULL;
336 UINT8 *VendorData = NULL;
337 UINT16 *InterruptList = NULL;
338 UINT16 *PinList = NULL;
339 UINT16 ResSourceLength;
340 UINT16 VendorLength;
341 UINT16 InterruptLength;
342 UINT16 DescriptorSize;
343 UINT32 CurrentByteOffset;
344 UINT32 PinCount = 0;
345 UINT32 i;
346
347
348 InitializerOp = Info->DescriptorTypeOp->Asl.Child;
349 CurrentByteOffset = Info->CurrentByteOffset;
350
351 /*
352 * Calculate lengths for fields that have variable length:
353 * 1) Resource Source string
354 * 2) Vendor Data buffer
355 * 3) PIN (interrupt) list
356 */
357 ResSourceLength = RsGetStringDataLength (InitializerOp);
358 VendorLength = RsGetBufferDataLength (InitializerOp);
359 InterruptLength = RsGetInterruptDataLength (InitializerOp, 10);
360
361 DescriptorSize = ACPI_AML_SIZE_LARGE (AML_RESOURCE_GPIO) +
362 ResSourceLength + VendorLength + InterruptLength;
363
364 /* Allocate the local resource node and initialize */
365
366 Rnode = RsAllocateResourceNode (DescriptorSize +
367 sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_LARGE_HEADER));
368
369 Descriptor = Rnode->Buffer;
370 Descriptor->Gpio.ResourceLength = DescriptorSize;
371 Descriptor->Gpio.DescriptorType = ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_GPIO;
372 Descriptor->Gpio.RevisionId = AML_RESOURCE_GPIO_REVISION;
373 Descriptor->Gpio.ConnectionType = AML_RESOURCE_GPIO_TYPE_INT;
374
375 /* Build pointers to optional areas */
376
377 InterruptList = ACPI_ADD_PTR (UINT16, Descriptor,
378 sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_GPIO));
379 PinList = InterruptList;
380 ResourceSource = ACPI_ADD_PTR (char, InterruptList, InterruptLength);
381 VendorData = ACPI_ADD_PTR (UINT8, ResourceSource, ResSourceLength);
382
383 /* Setup offsets within the descriptor */
384
385 Descriptor->Gpio.PinTableOffset = (UINT16)
386 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (InterruptList, Descriptor);
387
388 Descriptor->Gpio.ResSourceOffset = (UINT16)
389 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (ResourceSource, Descriptor);
390
391 /* Process all child initialization nodes */
392
393 for (i = 0; InitializerOp; i++)
394 {
395 switch (i)
396 {
397 case 0: /* Interrupt Mode - edge/level [Flag] (_MOD) */
398
399 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->Gpio.IntFlags, InitializerOp, 0, 0);
400 RsCreateBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_MODE,
401 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.IntFlags), 0);
402 break;
403
404 case 1: /* Interrupt Polarity - Active high/low [Flags] (_POL) */
405
406 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->Gpio.IntFlags, InitializerOp, 1, 0);
407 RsCreateMultiBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_POLARITY,
408 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.IntFlags), 1, 2);
409 break;
410
411 case 2: /* Share Type - Default: exclusive (0) [Flags] (_SHR) */
412
413 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->Gpio.IntFlags, InitializerOp, 3, 0);
414 RsCreateMultiBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_INTERRUPTSHARE,
415 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.IntFlags), 3, 2);
416 break;
417
418 case 3: /* Pin Config [BYTE] (_PPI) */
419
420 Descriptor->Gpio.PinConfig = (UINT8) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
421 RsCreateByteField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_PINCONFIG,
422 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.PinConfig));
423 break;
424
425 case 4: /* Debounce Timeout [WORD] (_DBT) */
426
427 Descriptor->Gpio.DebounceTimeout = (UINT16) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
428 RsCreateWordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_DEBOUNCETIME,
429 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.DebounceTimeout));
430 break;
431
432 case 5: /* ResSource [Optional Field - STRING] */
433
434 if (ResSourceLength)
435 {
436 /* Copy string to the descriptor */
437
438 strcpy (ResourceSource,
439 InitializerOp->Asl.Value.String);
440 }
441 break;
442
443 case 6: /* Resource Index */
444
445 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode != PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
446 {
447 Descriptor->Gpio.ResSourceIndex =
448 (UINT8) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
449 }
450 break;
451
452 case 7: /* Resource Usage (consumer/producer) */
453
454 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->Gpio.Flags, InitializerOp, 0, 1);
455 break;
456
457 case 8: /* Resource Tag (Descriptor Name) */
458
459 UtAttachNamepathToOwner (Info->DescriptorTypeOp, InitializerOp);
460 break;
461
462 case 9: /* Vendor Data (Optional - Buffer of BYTEs) (_VEN) */
463
464 /*
465 * Always set the VendorOffset even if there is no Vendor Data.
466 * This field is required in order to calculate the length
467 * of the ResourceSource at runtime.
468 */
469 Descriptor->Gpio.VendorOffset = (UINT16)
470 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (VendorData, Descriptor);
471
472 if (RsGetVendorData (InitializerOp, VendorData,
473 (CurrentByteOffset + Descriptor->Gpio.VendorOffset)))
474 {
475 Descriptor->Gpio.VendorLength = VendorLength;
476 }
477 break;
478
479 default:
480 /*
481 * PINs come through here, repeatedly. Each PIN must be a WORD.
482 * NOTE: there is no "length" field for this, so from ACPI spec:
483 * The number of pins in the table can be calculated from:
484 * PinCount = (Resource Source Name Offset - Pin Table Offset) / 2
485 * (implies resource source must immediately follow the pin list.)
486 * Name: _PIN
487 */
488 *InterruptList = (UINT16) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
489 InterruptList++;
490 PinCount++;
491
492 /* Case 10: First interrupt number in list */
493
494 if (i == 10)
495 {
496 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode == PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
497 {
498 /* Must be at least one interrupt */
499
500 AslError (ASL_ERROR, ASL_MSG_EX_INTERRUPT_LIST_MIN,
501 InitializerOp, NULL);
502 }
503
504 /* Check now for duplicates in list */
505
506 RsCheckListForDuplicates (InitializerOp);
507
508 /* Create a named field at the start of the list */
509
510 RsCreateWordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_PIN,
511 CurrentByteOffset + Descriptor->Gpio.PinTableOffset);
512 }
513 break;
514 }
515
516 InitializerOp = RsCompleteNodeAndGetNext (InitializerOp);
517 }
518
519 MpSaveGpioInfo (Info->MappingOp, Descriptor,
520 PinCount, PinList, ResourceSource);
521 return (Rnode);
522}

525/*******************************************************************************
526 *
527 * FUNCTION: RsDoGpioIoDescriptor
528 *
529 * PARAMETERS: Info - Parse Op and resource template offset
530 *
531 * RETURN: Completed resource node
532 *
533 * DESCRIPTION: Construct a long "GpioIo" descriptor
534 *
535 ******************************************************************************/
536
537ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *
538RsDoGpioIoDescriptor (
539 ASL_RESOURCE_INFO *Info)
540{
541 AML_RESOURCE *Descriptor;
542 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *InitializerOp;
543 ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *Rnode;
544 char *ResourceSource = NULL;
545 UINT8 *VendorData = NULL;
546 UINT16 *InterruptList = NULL;
547 UINT16 *PinList = NULL;
548 UINT16 ResSourceLength;
549 UINT16 VendorLength;
550 UINT16 InterruptLength;
551 UINT16 DescriptorSize;
552 UINT32 CurrentByteOffset;
553 UINT32 PinCount = 0;
554 UINT32 i;
555
556
557 InitializerOp = Info->DescriptorTypeOp->Asl.Child;
558 CurrentByteOffset = Info->CurrentByteOffset;
559
560 /*
561 * Calculate lengths for fields that have variable length:
562 * 1) Resource Source string
563 * 2) Vendor Data buffer
564 * 3) PIN (interrupt) list
565 */
566 ResSourceLength = RsGetStringDataLength (InitializerOp);
567 VendorLength = RsGetBufferDataLength (InitializerOp);
568 InterruptLength = RsGetInterruptDataLength (InitializerOp, 10);
569 PinList = InterruptList;
570
571 DescriptorSize = ACPI_AML_SIZE_LARGE (AML_RESOURCE_GPIO) +
572 ResSourceLength + VendorLength + InterruptLength;
573
574 /* Allocate the local resource node and initialize */
575
576 Rnode = RsAllocateResourceNode (DescriptorSize +
577 sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_LARGE_HEADER));
578
579 Descriptor = Rnode->Buffer;
580 Descriptor->Gpio.ResourceLength = DescriptorSize;
581 Descriptor->Gpio.DescriptorType = ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_GPIO;
582 Descriptor->Gpio.RevisionId = AML_RESOURCE_GPIO_REVISION;
583 Descriptor->Gpio.ConnectionType = AML_RESOURCE_GPIO_TYPE_IO;
584
585 /* Build pointers to optional areas */
586
587 InterruptList = ACPI_ADD_PTR (UINT16, Descriptor, sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_GPIO));
588 PinList = InterruptList;
589 ResourceSource = ACPI_ADD_PTR (char, InterruptList, InterruptLength);
590 VendorData = ACPI_ADD_PTR (UINT8, ResourceSource, ResSourceLength);
591
592 /* Setup offsets within the descriptor */
593
594 Descriptor->Gpio.PinTableOffset = (UINT16)
595 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (InterruptList, Descriptor);
596
597 Descriptor->Gpio.ResSourceOffset = (UINT16)
598 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (ResourceSource, Descriptor);
599
600 /* Process all child initialization nodes */
601
602 for (i = 0; InitializerOp; i++)
603 {
604 switch (i)
605 {
606 case 0: /* Share Type [Flags] (_SHR) */
607
608 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->Gpio.IntFlags, InitializerOp, 3, 0);
609 RsCreateBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_INTERRUPTSHARE,
610 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.IntFlags), 3);
611 break;
612
613 case 1: /* Pin Config [BYTE] (_PPI) */
614
615 Descriptor->Gpio.PinConfig = (UINT8) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
616 RsCreateByteField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_PINCONFIG,
617 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.PinConfig));
618 break;
619
620 case 2: /* Debounce Timeout [WORD] (_DBT) */
621
622 Descriptor->Gpio.DebounceTimeout = (UINT16) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
623 RsCreateWordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_DEBOUNCETIME,
624 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.DebounceTimeout));
625 break;
626
627 case 3: /* Drive Strength [WORD] (_DRS) */
628
629 Descriptor->Gpio.DriveStrength = (UINT16) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
630 RsCreateWordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_DRIVESTRENGTH,
631 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.DriveStrength));
632 break;
633
634 case 4: /* I/O Restriction [Flag] (_IOR) */
635
636 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->Gpio.IntFlags, InitializerOp, 0, 0);
637 RsCreateMultiBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_IORESTRICTION,
638 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (Gpio.IntFlags), 0, 2);
639 break;
640
641 case 5: /* ResSource [Optional Field - STRING] */
642
643 if (ResSourceLength)
644 {
645 /* Copy string to the descriptor */
646
647 strcpy (ResourceSource,
648 InitializerOp->Asl.Value.String);
649 }
650 break;
651
652 case 6: /* Resource Index */
653
654 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode != PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
655 {
656 Descriptor->Gpio.ResSourceIndex = (UINT8) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
657 }
658 break;
659
660 case 7: /* Resource Usage (consumer/producer) */
661
662 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->Gpio.Flags, InitializerOp, 0, 1);
663 break;
664
665 case 8: /* Resource Tag (Descriptor Name) */
666
667 UtAttachNamepathToOwner (Info->DescriptorTypeOp, InitializerOp);
668 break;
669
670 case 9: /* Vendor Data (Optional - Buffer of BYTEs) (_VEN) */
671 /*
672 * Always set the VendorOffset even if there is no Vendor Data.
673 * This field is required in order to calculate the length
674 * of the ResourceSource at runtime.
675 */
676 Descriptor->Gpio.VendorOffset = (UINT16)
677 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (VendorData, Descriptor);
678
679 if (RsGetVendorData (InitializerOp, VendorData,
680 (CurrentByteOffset + Descriptor->Gpio.VendorOffset)))
681 {
682 Descriptor->Gpio.VendorLength = VendorLength;
683 }
684 break;
685
686 default:
687 /*
688 * PINs come through here, repeatedly. Each PIN must be a WORD.
689 * NOTE: there is no "length" field for this, so from ACPI spec:
690 * The number of pins in the table can be calculated from:
691 * PinCount = (Resource Source Name Offset - Pin Table Offset) / 2
692 * (implies resource source must immediately follow the pin list.)
693 * Name: _PIN
694 */
695 *InterruptList = (UINT16) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
696 InterruptList++;
697 PinCount++;
698
699 /* Case 10: First interrupt number in list */
700
701 if (i == 10)
702 {
703 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode == PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
704 {
705 /* Must be at least one interrupt */
706
707 AslError (ASL_ERROR, ASL_MSG_EX_INTERRUPT_LIST_MIN,
708 InitializerOp, NULL);
709 }
710
711 /* Check now for duplicates in list */
712
713 RsCheckListForDuplicates (InitializerOp);
714
715 /* Create a named field at the start of the list */
716
717 RsCreateWordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_PIN,
718 CurrentByteOffset + Descriptor->Gpio.PinTableOffset);
719 }
720 break;
721 }
722
723 InitializerOp = RsCompleteNodeAndGetNext (InitializerOp);
724 }
725
726 MpSaveGpioInfo (Info->MappingOp, Descriptor,
727 PinCount, PinList, ResourceSource);
728 return (Rnode);
729}

732/*******************************************************************************
733 *
734 * FUNCTION: RsDoI2cSerialBusDescriptor
735 *
736 * PARAMETERS: Info - Parse Op and resource template offset
737 *
738 * RETURN: Completed resource node
739 *
740 * DESCRIPTION: Construct a long "I2cSerialBus" descriptor
741 *
742 ******************************************************************************/
743
744ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *
745RsDoI2cSerialBusDescriptor (
746 ASL_RESOURCE_INFO *Info)
747{
748 AML_RESOURCE *Descriptor;
749 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *InitializerOp;
750 ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *Rnode;
751 char *ResourceSource = NULL;
752 UINT8 *VendorData = NULL;
753 UINT16 ResSourceLength;
754 UINT16 VendorLength;
755 UINT16 DescriptorSize;
756 UINT32 CurrentByteOffset;
757 UINT32 i;
758
759
760 InitializerOp = Info->DescriptorTypeOp->Asl.Child;
761 CurrentByteOffset = Info->CurrentByteOffset;
762
763 /*
764 * Calculate lengths for fields that have variable length:
765 * 1) Resource Source string
766 * 2) Vendor Data buffer
767 */
768 ResSourceLength = RsGetStringDataLength (InitializerOp);
769 VendorLength = RsGetBufferDataLength (InitializerOp);
770
771 DescriptorSize = ACPI_AML_SIZE_LARGE (AML_RESOURCE_I2C_SERIALBUS) +
772 ResSourceLength + VendorLength;
773
774 /* Allocate the local resource node and initialize */
775
776 Rnode = RsAllocateResourceNode (DescriptorSize +
777 sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_LARGE_HEADER));
778
779 Descriptor = Rnode->Buffer;
780 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.ResourceLength = DescriptorSize;
781 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.DescriptorType = ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_SERIAL_BUS;
782 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.RevisionId = AML_RESOURCE_I2C_REVISION;
783 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.TypeRevisionId = AML_RESOURCE_I2C_TYPE_REVISION;
784 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.Type = AML_RESOURCE_I2C_SERIALBUSTYPE;
785 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.TypeDataLength = AML_RESOURCE_I2C_MIN_DATA_LEN + VendorLength;
786
787 if (Info->DescriptorTypeOp->Asl.ParseOpcode == PARSEOP_I2C_SERIALBUS_V2)
788 {
789 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.RevisionId = 2;
790 }
791
792 /* Build pointers to optional areas */
793
794 VendorData = ACPI_ADD_PTR (UINT8, Descriptor, sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_I2C_SERIALBUS));
795 ResourceSource = ACPI_ADD_PTR (char, VendorData, VendorLength);
796
797 /* Process all child initialization nodes */
798
799 for (i = 0; InitializerOp; i++)
800 {
801 switch (i)
802 {
803 case 0: /* Slave Address [WORD] (_ADR) */
804
805 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.SlaveAddress = (UINT16) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
806 RsCreateWordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_ADDRESS,
807 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (I2cSerialBus.SlaveAddress));
808 break;
809
810 case 1: /* Slave Mode [Flag] (_SLV) */
811
812 RsSetFlagBits (&Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.Flags, InitializerOp, 0, 0);
813 RsCreateBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_SLAVEMODE,
814 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (I2cSerialBus.Flags), 0);
815 break;
816
817 case 2: /* Connection Speed [DWORD] (_SPE) */
818
819 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.ConnectionSpeed = (UINT32) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
820 RsCreateDwordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_SPEED,
821 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (I2cSerialBus.ConnectionSpeed));
822 break;
823
824 case 3: /* Addressing Mode [Flag] (_MOD) */
825
826 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.TypeSpecificFlags, InitializerOp, 0, 0);
827 RsCreateBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_MODE,
828 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (I2cSerialBus.TypeSpecificFlags), 0);
829 break;
830
831 case 4: /* ResSource [Optional Field - STRING] */
832
833 if (ResSourceLength)
834 {
835 /* Copy string to the descriptor */
836
837 strcpy (ResourceSource,
838 InitializerOp->Asl.Value.String);
839 }
840 break;
841
842 case 5: /* Resource Index */
843
844 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode != PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
845 {
846 Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.ResSourceIndex =
847 (UINT8) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
848 }
849 break;
850
851 case 6: /* Resource Usage (consumer/producer) */
852
853 RsSetFlagBits (&Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.Flags, InitializerOp, 1, 1);
854 break;
855
856 case 7: /* Resource Tag (Descriptor Name) */
857
858 UtAttachNamepathToOwner (Info->DescriptorTypeOp, InitializerOp);
859 break;
860
861 case 8:
862 /*
863 * Connection Share - Added for V2 (ACPI 6.0) version of the descriptor
864 * Note: For V1, the share bit will be zero (Op is DEFAULT_ARG from
865 * the ASL parser)
866 */
867 RsSetFlagBits (&Descriptor->I2cSerialBus.Flags, InitializerOp, 2, 0);
868 RsCreateBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_INTERRUPTSHARE,
869 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (I2cSerialBus.Flags), 2);
870 break;
871
872 case 9: /* Vendor Data (Optional - Buffer of BYTEs) (_VEN) */
873
874 RsGetVendorData (InitializerOp, VendorData,
875 CurrentByteOffset + sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_I2C_SERIALBUS));
876 break;
877
878 default: /* Ignore any extra nodes */
879
880 break;
881 }
882
883 InitializerOp = RsCompleteNodeAndGetNext (InitializerOp);
884 }
885
886 MpSaveSerialInfo (Info->MappingOp, Descriptor, ResourceSource);
887 return (Rnode);
888}

1125
1126 Descriptor = Rnode->Buffer;

1194 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->UartSerialBus.TypeSpecificFlags, InitializerOp, 0, 0);
1195 RsCreateMultiBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_FLOWCONTROL,

1283/*******************************************************************************
1284 *
1285 * FUNCTION: RsDoPinFunctionDescriptor
1286 *
1287 * PARAMETERS: Info - Parse Op and resource template offset
1288 *
1289 * RETURN: Completed resource node
1290 *
1291 * DESCRIPTION: Construct a long "PinFunction" descriptor
1292 *
1293 ******************************************************************************/
1294
1295ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *
1296RsDoPinFunctionDescriptor (
1297 ASL_RESOURCE_INFO *Info)
1298{
1299 AML_RESOURCE *Descriptor;
1300 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *InitializerOp;
1301 ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *Rnode;
1302 char *ResourceSource = NULL;
1303 UINT8 *VendorData = NULL;
1304 UINT16 *PinList = NULL;
1305 UINT16 ResSourceLength;
1306 UINT16 VendorLength;
1307 UINT16 PinListLength;
1308 UINT16 DescriptorSize;
1309 UINT32 CurrentByteOffset;
1310 UINT32 PinCount = 0;
1311 UINT32 i;
1312
1313 InitializerOp = Info->DescriptorTypeOp->Asl.Child;
1314 CurrentByteOffset = Info->CurrentByteOffset;
1315
1316 /*
1317 * Calculate lengths for fields that have variable length:
1318 * 1) Resource Source string
1319 * 2) Vendor Data buffer
1320 * 3) PIN (interrupt) list
1321 */
1322 ResSourceLength = RsGetStringDataLength (InitializerOp);
1323 VendorLength = RsGetBufferDataLength (InitializerOp);
1324 PinListLength = RsGetInterruptDataLength (InitializerOp, 8);
1325
1326 DescriptorSize = ACPI_AML_SIZE_LARGE (AML_RESOURCE_PIN_FUNCTION) +
1327 ResSourceLength + VendorLength + PinListLength;
1328
1329 /* Allocate the local resource node and initialize */
1330
1331 Rnode = RsAllocateResourceNode (DescriptorSize +
1332 sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_LARGE_HEADER));
1333
1334 Descriptor = Rnode->Buffer;
1335 Descriptor->PinFunction.ResourceLength = DescriptorSize;
1336 Descriptor->PinFunction.DescriptorType = ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_PIN_FUNCTION;
1337 Descriptor->PinFunction.RevisionId = AML_RESOURCE_PIN_FUNCTION_REVISION;
1338
1339 /* Build pointers to optional areas */
1340
1341 PinList = ACPI_ADD_PTR (UINT16, Descriptor, sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_PIN_FUNCTION));
1342 ResourceSource = ACPI_ADD_PTR (char, PinList, PinListLength);
1343 VendorData = ACPI_ADD_PTR (UINT8, ResourceSource, ResSourceLength);
1344
1345 /* Setup offsets within the descriptor */
1346
1347 Descriptor->PinFunction.PinTableOffset = (UINT16)
1348 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (PinList, Descriptor);
1349
1350 Descriptor->PinFunction.ResSourceOffset = (UINT16)
1351 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (ResourceSource, Descriptor);
1352
1353 /* Process all child initialization nodes */
1354
1355 for (i = 0; InitializerOp; i++)
1356 {
1357 switch (i)
1358 {
1359 case 0: /* Share Type [Flags] (_SHR) */
1360
1361 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->PinFunction.Flags, InitializerOp, 0, 0);
1362 RsCreateBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_INTERRUPTSHARE,
1363 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (PinFunction.Flags), 0);
1364 break;
1365
1366 case 1: /* Pin Config [BYTE] (_PPI) */
1367
1368 Descriptor->PinFunction.PinConfig = (UINT8) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
1369 RsCreateByteField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_PINCONFIG,
1370 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (PinFunction.PinConfig));
1371 break;
1372
1373 case 2: /* Function Number [WORD] (_FUN) */
1374
1375 Descriptor->PinFunction.FunctionNumber = (UINT16) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
1376 RsCreateDwordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_FUNCTION,
1377 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (PinFunction.FunctionNumber));
1378 break;
1379
1380 case 3: /* ResSource [Optional Field - STRING] */
1381
1382 if (ResSourceLength)
1383 {
1384 /* Copy string to the descriptor */
1385
1386 strcpy (ResourceSource, InitializerOp->Asl.Value.String);
1387 }
1388 break;
1389
1390 case 4: /* Resource Index */
1391
1392 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode != PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
1393 {
1394 Descriptor->PinFunction.ResSourceIndex = (UINT8) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
1395 }
1396 break;
1397
1398 case 5: /* Resource Usage (consumer/producer) */
1399
1400 /* Assumed to be consumer */
1401
1402 break;
1403
1404 case 6: /* Resource Tag (Descriptor Name) */
1405
1406 UtAttachNamepathToOwner (Info->DescriptorTypeOp, InitializerOp);
1407 break;
1408
1409 case 7: /* Vendor Data (Optional - Buffer of BYTEs) (_VEN) */
1410 /*
1411 * Always set the VendorOffset even if there is no Vendor Data.
1412 * This field is required in order to calculate the length
1413 * of the ResourceSource at runtime.
1414 */
1415 Descriptor->PinFunction.VendorOffset = (UINT16)
1416 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (VendorData, Descriptor);
1417
1418 if (RsGetVendorData (InitializerOp, VendorData,
1419 (CurrentByteOffset + Descriptor->PinFunction.VendorOffset)))
1420 {
1421 Descriptor->PinFunction.VendorLength = VendorLength;
1422 }
1423 break;
1424
1425 default:
1426 /*
1427 * PINs come through here, repeatedly. Each PIN must be a WORD.
1428 * NOTE: there is no "length" field for this, so from ACPI spec:
1429 * The number of pins in the table can be calculated from:
1430 * PinCount = (Resource Source Name Offset - Pin Table Offset) / 2
1431 * (implies resource source must immediately follow the pin list.)
1432 * Name: _PIN
1433 */
1434 *PinList = (UINT16) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
1435 PinList++;
1436 PinCount++;
1437
1438 /* Case 8: First pin number in list */
1439
1440 if (i == 8)
1441 {
1442 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode == PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
1443 {
1444 /* Must be at least one interrupt */
1445
1446 AslError (ASL_ERROR, ASL_MSG_EX_INTERRUPT_LIST_MIN,
1447 InitializerOp, NULL);
1448 }
1449
1450 /* Check now for duplicates in list */
1451
1452 RsCheckListForDuplicates (InitializerOp);
1453
1454 /* Create a named field at the start of the list */
1455
1456 RsCreateWordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_PIN,
1457 CurrentByteOffset + Descriptor->PinFunction.PinTableOffset);
1458 }
1459 break;

1469/*******************************************************************************
1470 *
1471 * FUNCTION: RsDoPinConfigDescriptor
1472 *
1473 * PARAMETERS: Info - Parse Op and resource template offset
1474 *
1475 * RETURN: Completed resource node
1476 *
1477 * DESCRIPTION: Construct a long "PinConfig" descriptor
1478 *
1479 ******************************************************************************/
1480
1481ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *
1482RsDoPinConfigDescriptor (
1483 ASL_RESOURCE_INFO *Info)
1484{
1485 AML_RESOURCE *Descriptor;
1486 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *InitializerOp;
1487 ASL_RESOURCE_NODE *Rnode;
1488 char *ResourceSource = NULL;
1489 UINT8 *VendorData = NULL;
1490 UINT16 *PinList = NULL;
1491 UINT16 ResSourceLength;
1492 UINT16 VendorLength;
1493 UINT16 PinListLength;
1494 UINT16 DescriptorSize;
1495 UINT32 CurrentByteOffset;
1496 UINT32 PinCount = 0;
1497 UINT32 i;
1498
1499 InitializerOp = Info->DescriptorTypeOp->Asl.Child;
1500 CurrentByteOffset = Info->CurrentByteOffset;
1501
1502 /*
1503 * Calculate lengths for fields that have variable length:
1504 * 1) Resource Source string
1505 * 2) Vendor Data buffer
1506 * 3) PIN (interrupt) list
1507 */
1508 ResSourceLength = RsGetStringDataLength (InitializerOp);
1509 VendorLength = RsGetBufferDataLength (InitializerOp);
1510 PinListLength = RsGetInterruptDataLength (InitializerOp, 8);
1511
1512 DescriptorSize = ACPI_AML_SIZE_LARGE (AML_RESOURCE_PIN_CONFIG) +
1513 ResSourceLength + VendorLength + PinListLength;
1514
1515 /* Allocate the local resource node and initialize */
1516
1517 Rnode = RsAllocateResourceNode (DescriptorSize +
1518 sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_LARGE_HEADER));
1519
1520 Descriptor = Rnode->Buffer;
1521 Descriptor->PinConfig.ResourceLength = DescriptorSize;
1522 Descriptor->PinConfig.DescriptorType = ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_PIN_CONFIG;
1523 Descriptor->PinConfig.RevisionId = AML_RESOURCE_PIN_CONFIG_REVISION;
1524
1525 /* Build pointers to optional areas */
1526
1527 PinList = ACPI_ADD_PTR (UINT16, Descriptor, sizeof (AML_RESOURCE_PIN_CONFIG));
1528 ResourceSource = ACPI_ADD_PTR (char, PinList, PinListLength);
1529 VendorData = ACPI_ADD_PTR (UINT8, ResourceSource, ResSourceLength);
1530
1531 /* Setup offsets within the descriptor */
1532
1533 Descriptor->PinConfig.PinTableOffset = (UINT16)
1534 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (PinList, Descriptor);
1535
1536 Descriptor->PinConfig.ResSourceOffset = (UINT16)
1537 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (ResourceSource, Descriptor);
1538
1539 /* Process all child initialization nodes */
1540
1541 for (i = 0; InitializerOp; i++)
1542 {
1543 BOOLEAN isValid;
1544
1545 switch (i)
1546 {
1547 case 0: /* Share Type [Flags] (_SHR) */
1548
1549 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->PinConfig.Flags, InitializerOp, 0, 0);
1550 RsCreateBitField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_INTERRUPTSHARE,
1551 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (PinConfig.Flags), 0);
1552 break;
1553
1554 case 1: /* Pin Config Type [BYTE] (_TYP) */
1555
1556 isValid = InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer <= 0x0d;
1557 if (!isValid)
1558 {
1559 isValid = InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer >= 0x80 &&
1560 InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer <= 0xff;
1561 }
1562 if (!isValid)
1563 {
1564 AslError (ASL_ERROR, ASL_MSG_RANGE, InitializerOp, NULL);
1565 }
1566
1567 Descriptor->PinConfig.PinConfigType = (UINT8) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
1568 RsCreateByteField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_PINCONFIG_TYPE,
1569 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (PinConfig.PinConfigType));
1570
1571 break;
1572
1573 case 2: /* Pin Config Value [DWORD] (_VAL) */
1574
1575 Descriptor->PinConfig.PinConfigValue = (UINT32) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
1576 RsCreateDwordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_PINCONFIG_VALUE,
1577 CurrentByteOffset + ASL_RESDESC_OFFSET (PinConfig.PinConfigValue));
1578 break;
1579
1580 case 3: /* ResSource [Optional Field - STRING] */
1581
1582 if (ResSourceLength)
1583 {
1584 /* Copy string to the descriptor */
1585
1586 strcpy (ResourceSource, InitializerOp->Asl.Value.String);
1587 }
1588 break;
1589
1590 case 4: /* Resource Index */
1591
1592 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode != PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
1593 {
1594 Descriptor->PinConfig.ResSourceIndex = (UINT8) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
1595 }
1596 break;
1597
1598 case 5: /* Resource Usage (consumer/producer) */
1599
1600 RsSetFlagBits16 (&Descriptor->PinConfig.Flags, InitializerOp, 1, 1);
1601
1602 break;
1603
1604 case 6: /* Resource Tag (Descriptor Name) */
1605
1606 UtAttachNamepathToOwner (Info->DescriptorTypeOp, InitializerOp);
1607 break;
1608
1609 case 7: /* Vendor Data (Optional - Buffer of BYTEs) (_VEN) */
1610 /*
1611 * Always set the VendorOffset even if there is no Vendor Data.
1612 * This field is required in order to calculate the length
1613 * of the ResourceSource at runtime.
1614 */
1615 Descriptor->PinConfig.VendorOffset = (UINT16)
1616 ACPI_PTR_DIFF (VendorData, Descriptor);
1617
1618 if (RsGetVendorData (InitializerOp, VendorData,
1619 (CurrentByteOffset + Descriptor->PinConfig.VendorOffset)))
1620 {
1621 Descriptor->PinConfig.VendorLength = VendorLength;
1622 }
1623 break;
1624
1625 default:
1626 /*
1627 * PINs come through here, repeatedly. Each PIN must be a WORD.
1628 * NOTE: there is no "length" field for this, so from ACPI spec:
1629 * The number of pins in the table can be calculated from:
1630 * PinCount = (Resource Source Name Offset - Pin Table Offset) / 2
1631 * (implies resource source must immediately follow the pin list.)
1632 * Name: _PIN
1633 */
1634 *PinList = (UINT16) InitializerOp->Asl.Value.Integer;
1635 PinList++;
1636 PinCount++;
1637
1638 /* Case 8: First pin number in list */
1639
1640 if (i == 8)
1641 {
1642 if (InitializerOp->Asl.ParseOpcode == PARSEOP_DEFAULT_ARG)
1643 {
1644 /* Must be at least one interrupt */
1645
1646 AslError (ASL_ERROR, ASL_MSG_EX_INTERRUPT_LIST_MIN,
1647 InitializerOp, NULL);
1648 }
1649
1650 /* Check now for duplicates in list */
1651
1652 RsCheckListForDuplicates (InitializerOp);
1653
1654 /* Create a named field at the start of the list */
1655
1656 RsCreateWordField (InitializerOp, ACPI_RESTAG_PIN,
1657 CurrentByteOffset + Descriptor->PinConfig.PinTableOffset);
1658 }
1659 break;
1660 }
1661
1662 InitializerOp = RsCompleteNodeAndGetNext (InitializerOp);
1663 }
1664
1665 return (Rnode);
1666}
